# The image builds from source and compiles fresh inside the build stage, so none
# of the local build output, installed dependencies, runtime state, or private
# material is sent to the daemon — a smaller, faster, and cleaner build context.

# dependencies & build output (reinstalled / recompiled in the image)
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/*.tsbuildinfo
.bun/

# local runtime state & secrets — must never enter an image
.asterism/
.claude/
*.db
*.db-journal
*.sqlite
.env
.env.*

# version control & CI
.git/
.github/

# docs site build + private/internal material (not for a published image)
site/
internal/
landing/
docs/
CONTEXT_HANDOFF.md
ROADMAP.md
PROJECT_INSTRUCTIONS.md
STARTER_PROMPTS.md
CLAUDE_INTERNAL.md
TASKS.md

# editor / OS
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/

# the image-build inputs themselves
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
